<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p class="p">To get the background information on the changes in corn spatial distribution pattern, we develop a stability index (
 <italic class="italic">SI</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">s</italic>
 </sub>) by:
 <disp-formula id="Equ1" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">1</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M1" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$S{I}_{s}=\frac{{\sum }_{c}^{m}{({A}_{c,y}^{usda}-{A}_{c,y0}^{usda})}^{2}}{{\sum }_{c}^{m}{A}_{c,y0}^{usda}/m}\,\,c=1\ldots m$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M2" display="block" class="math">
    <mi class="mi">S</mi>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">I</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">s</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msubsup class="msubsup">
       <mo class="mo">∑</mo>
       <mi class="mi">c</mi>
       <mi class="mi">m</mi>
      </msubsup>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msup class="msup">
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo stretchy="true" class="mo">(</mo>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <msubsup class="msubsup">
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mi class="mi">A</mi>
           </mrow>
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mi class="mi">c</mi>
            <mo class="mo">,</mo>
            <mi class="mi">y</mi>
           </mrow>
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mi class="mi">u</mi>
            <mi class="mi">s</mi>
            <mi class="mi">d</mi>
            <mi class="mi">a</mi>
           </mrow>
          </msubsup>
          <mo class="mo">−</mo>
          <msubsup class="msubsup">
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mi class="mi">A</mi>
           </mrow>
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mi class="mi">c</mi>
            <mo class="mo">,</mo>
            <mi class="mi">y</mi>
            <mn class="mn">0</mn>
           </mrow>
           <mrow class="mrow">
            <mi class="mi">u</mi>
            <mi class="mi">s</mi>
            <mi class="mi">d</mi>
            <mi class="mi">a</mi>
           </mrow>
          </msubsup>
         </mrow>
         <mo stretchy="true" class="mo">)</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mn class="mn">2</mn>
       </msup>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msubsup class="msubsup">
       <mo class="mo">∑</mo>
       <mi class="mi">c</mi>
       <mi class="mi">m</mi>
      </msubsup>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msubsup class="msubsup">
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">A</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">c</mi>
         <mo class="mo">,</mo>
         <mi class="mi">y</mi>
         <mn class="mn">0</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">u</mi>
         <mi class="mi">s</mi>
         <mi class="mi">d</mi>
         <mi class="mi">a</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msubsup>
       <mo class="mo">/</mo>
       <mi class="mi">m</mi>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <mspace width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
    <mspace width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
    <mi class="mi">c</mi>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mn class="mn">1</mn>
    <mi class="mi">…</mi>
    <mi class="mi">m</mi>
   </math>
   <graphic xlink:href="41598_2017_1599_Article_Equ1.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>Where 
 <inline-formula id="IEq1" class="inline-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M3" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${A}_{c,y}^{usda}\,$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M4" class="math">
    <msubsup class="msubsup">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">A</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">c</mi>
      <mo class="mo">,</mo>
      <mi class="mi">y</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">u</mi>
      <mi class="mi">s</mi>
      <mi class="mi">d</mi>
      <mi class="mi">a</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msubsup>
    <mspace width=".25em" class="mspace"/>
   </math>
   <inline-graphic xlink:href="41598_2017_1599_Article_IEq1.gif" class="inline-graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula>is the total corn area for county 
 <italic class="italic">c</italic> from USDA census. 
 <italic class="italic">s</italic> is the state, 
 <italic class="italic">y</italic> is for the year while 
 <italic class="italic">y</italic>0 is the reference year 2000. Larger 
 <italic class="italic">SI</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">s</italic>
 </sub> means larger instability (changes) of crop spatial distribution pattern between counties within this state and vice versa. It should be noted that crop yield stability is a broad topic and there are generally two dimensions involved when referring to yield stability: its temporal and spatial stability. As for the temporal stability, the standard deviation and the coefficient of variation (CV) are commonly used index to measure yield stability over time
 <sup class="sup">
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR20" class="xref">20</xref>, 
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR36" class="xref">36</xref>, 
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR54" class="xref">54</xref>
 </sup>. There are also more complex index for measuring the temporal stability of crop yield, e.g. the ecovalence index, the stability variance index and the yield stability index
 <sup class="sup">
  <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR55" class="xref">55</xref>
 </sup>. Here, we refers to the stability of crop spatial distribution pattern and the evolutions of spatial stability as indicated by the index is shown in Fig. 
 <xref rid="Fig1" ref-type="fig" class="xref">1b</xref>.
</p>
